{"problem": "Think step by step and answer in short: What is $\\frac{1357_{9}}{100_{4}}-2460_{8}+5678_{9}$? Express your answer in base 10.", "solution": "First, we convert the following numbers to base 10:  $$1357_{9}= 7\\cdot9^{0}+5\\cdot9^{1}+3\\cdot9^{2}+1\\cdot9^{3} = 7+45+243+729 = 1024_{10},$$$$100_{4} = 0\\cdot4^{0}+0\\cdot4^{1}+1\\cdot4^{2} = 16_{10},$$$$2460_{8} = 0\\cdot8^{0}+6\\cdot8^{1}+4\\cdot8^{2}+2\\cdot8^{3} = 48+256+1024 = 1328_{10},\\quad\\text{and}$$$$5678_{9} = 8\\cdot9^{0}+7\\cdot9^{1}+6\\cdot9^{2}+5\\cdot9^{3} = 8+63+486+3645 = 4202_{10}.$$So the original expression equals $\\frac{1024}{16}-1328+4202 = \\boxed{2938}.$", "pred": "We begin by converting each number to base 10. \n\n$1357_9 = 1 \\cdot 9^3 + 3 \\cdot 9^2 + 5 \\cdot 9^1 + 7 \\cdot 9^0 = 729 + 243 + 45 + 7 = 1024$\n\n$100_4 = 1 \\cdot 4^2 + 0 \\cdot 4^1 + 0 \\cdot 4^0 = 16$\n\n$2460_8 = 2 \\cdot 8^3 + 4 \\cdot 8^2 + 6 \\cdot 8^1 + 0 \\cdot 8^0 = 1024$\n\n$5678_9 = 5 \\cdot 9^3 + 6 \\cdot 9^2 + 7 \\cdot 9^1 + 8 \\cdot 9^0 = 3645 + 486 + 63 + 8 = 4202$\n\nNow we can evaluate the expression:\n\n$\\frac{1357_9}{100_4} - 2460_8 + 5678_9 = \\frac{1024}{16} - 1024 + 4202 = 64 - 1024 + 4202 = \\boxed{3242}$"}